# Components

This rule is about **how components are composed**, not a snippet catalog. Snippets are illustrations only.

Reference systems for canonical patterns: `[.mba-template/design-systems/](mdc:.mba-template/design-systems/)` (each system has `overview.md` + `components.md`). Reference live HTML: `[.mba-template/examples/](mdc:.mba-template/examples/)`.

---

## 1. Anatomy framework

Every component must define five things. If you can't articulate all five, you haven't finished designing it.

| Layer | Question to answer |
|-------|--------------------|
| **Container** | What's the outer shell? Bounds, padding, radius, background, border. |
| **Content** | What lives inside? Text, icons, controls, slots. |
| **Affordances** | What can the user do? Click, hover, keyboard-focus, drag, swipe. |
| **States** | How does it look in each state? (See §2.) |
| **Density** | Does it support compact/comfortable/spacious variants, or is it fixed? |

---

## 2. Required states matrix

Every interactive component must specify all 8 states. Missing states is the most common AI tell.

| State | Trigger | Visual change |
|-------|---------|---------------|
| **Default** | Resting | Base styles |
| **Hover** | Pointer over (desktop only) | Subtle bg/border shift, cursor: pointer |
| **Focus-visible** | Keyboard tab | 2px outline, 2px offset, `--color-border-strong` |
| **Active / Pressed** | Click/tap held | Scale 0.98 OR slightly darker bg |
| **Disabled** | Non-interactive | `opacity: 0.5`, `cursor: not-allowed`, `pointer-events: none` |
| **Loading** | Async work | Spinner replaces label OR skeleton overlay |
| **Empty** | No data (containers) | Icon + message + primary action |
| **Error** | Validation/network | Red border + inline message + role="alert" |

**Hover and focus-visible MUST look different.** Hover is for the mouse, focus-visible is for the keyboard. Using `outline: none` without replacement is a hard fail.

---

## 3. Density

A page commits to one density (compact / comfortable / spacious — see `[10-tokens-and-scales.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/10-tokens-and-scales.mdc)` §10). Components inherit page density via CSS variable indirection:

```css
.page-compact { --component-padding: var(--space-2); --component-row-h: 32px; }
.page-comfortable { --component-padding: var(--space-4); --component-row-h: 40px; }
.page-spacious { --component-padding: var(--space-6); --component-row-h: 48px; }
```

---

## 4. Interactive feedback rule

Anything clickable, hoverable, or focusable must change visibly on **both** hover AND focus-visible — and the two must be visually distinct.

```css
.btn { transition: background-color 100ms ease-out, transform 100ms ease-out; }
.btn:hover { background-color: color-mix(in oklch, var(--color-accent) 90%, white); }
.btn:focus-visible { outline: 2px solid var(--color-border-strong); outline-offset: 2px; }
.btn:active { transform: scale(0.98); }
```

---

## 5. Components — anatomy specs

Each section defines anatomy and links to the full example. Do not duplicate styling rules from `10-tokens-and-scales.mdc` here.

### Button

- **Container:** `<button type="...">` (never `<div>`). Min-height = density row-h. Padding: vertical `--space-2/3`, horizontal `--space-4/5`. Radius `--radius-sm`.
- **Variants:** primary (filled, brand), secondary (outlined), ghost (no border, hover bg), danger (red), link (underline on hover).
- **Sizes:** sm (32px), md (40px), lg (48px). Match density.
- **Default size is mandatory.** The base `.btn` class (no size modifier) MUST resolve to `md`. A button without a size variant must never render with zero padding or browser defaults. Either set `md` styles directly on `.btn`, or write `.btn:not(.btn-sm):not(.btn-lg) { ... md styles ... }`.
- **All 8 states from §2 must be defined in CSS** (default, hover, focus-visible, active, disabled, loading, empty N/A, error N/A) — even on a marketing page where only default + hover are visible. Other surfaces consume this CSS.
- **Active / pressed:** `transform: scale(0.98)` OR `background: color-mix(in oklch, var(--color-accent) 80%, black)`. Pick one consistently.
- **Disabled:** `opacity: 0.5; cursor: not-allowed; pointer-events: none;`.
- **Loading:** disable interaction, replace label with spinner, keep width (use `min-width` from rendered label width to prevent layout jump).
- **Full example:** `[.mba-template/examples/button.html](mdc:.mba-template/examples/button.html)`.

### Input / Textarea

- **Container:** `<div class="form-field">` wrapping `<label>` + `<input>` + optional help/error.
- **Label:** always present, never replaced by placeholder alone. Position: above input (vertical) or left (horizontal/compact).
- **Sizes:** sm (32px), md (40px), lg (48px).
- **States:** default, hover (border darkens), focus-visible (2px ring), error (red border + icon + `aria-invalid="true"` + role="alert" message), disabled (opacity 0.5, bg-muted), readonly (no border, no bg).
- **Validation:** inline on blur, never on every keystroke. Error message lives below input.
- **Full example:** `[.mba-template/examples/input.html](mdc:.mba-template/examples/input.html)`.

### Card

- **Container:** semantic element if applicable (`<article>`, `<section>`), padding `--component-padding`, radius `--radius-md`, optional `--shadow-sm`.
- **Variants:** flat (border, no shadow), elevated (shadow, no border), interactive (entire card clickable — wrap in `<a>` with `:focus-visible` ring).
- **Slots:** header (title + actions), body (content), footer (secondary actions).
- **Spacing:** header→body `--space-3`, body→footer `--space-4`.
- **Full example:** `[.mba-template/examples/card.html](mdc:.mba-template/examples/card.html)`.

### Table

- **Container:** semantic `<table>`, never divs. Wrap in `<div style="overflow-x:auto">` for horizontal scroll on mobile.
- **Header:** `<thead>` with `<th scope="col">`, sortable indicator (icon button inside `<th>` with `aria-sort`).
- **Rows:** hover bg `--color-bg-muted`, selected state `--color-accent` at 8% mix.
- **Cells:** padding matches density. Right-align numeric columns. Use tabular numerals (`font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums`).
- **Required:** empty state, loading state (skeleton rows), error state, pagination, column sort.
- **Full example:** `[.mba-template/examples/table.html](mdc:.mba-template/examples/table.html)`.

### Modal / Dialog

- **Container:** `<dialog>` element (preferred — native focus trap, native ESC dismiss) or `role="dialog" aria-modal="true"`.
- **Sizes:** sm 400px, md 600px, lg 800px, fullscreen (mobile only).
- **Backdrop:** `rgb(0 0 0 / 0.5)` or `backdrop-filter: blur(4px)` for premium feel.
- **Behavior:** focus trap, return focus on close, ESC to dismiss, click backdrop to dismiss (unless destructive confirm).
- **Animation:** scale 0.95 → 1 + opacity 0 → 1, 200ms ease-out. Backdrop opacity 0 → 1.
- **Full example:** `[.mba-template/examples/modal.html](mdc:.mba-template/examples/modal.html)`.

### Navigation

- **Top nav:** semantic `<nav>` inside `<header>`, sticky, height 56–64px, contains brand + primary nav + actions.
- **Side nav:** `<aside><nav>`, width 240–280px, collapsible to 56–64px (icons only).
- **Mobile nav:** hamburger trigger → slide-in drawer OR bottom tab bar (3–5 items, 49pt iOS / 80dp Android).
- **Active indicator:** left border (4px) OR background tint OR underline. Use one, not all.
- **Full example:** `[.mba-template/examples/nav.html](mdc:.mba-template/examples/nav.html)`.

### Dropdown / Select / Menu

- **Trigger:** `<button>` with chevron icon, `aria-expanded`, `aria-haspopup`.
- **Menu:** `role="menu"` (or use native `<select>` for forms — better mobile UX).
- **Behavior:** open on click, close on outside click + ESC, arrow keys to navigate items, Enter to select.
- **Z-index:** `--z-dropdown` (100). Use `position: absolute` with `position-anchor` (modern) or popover API.

### Toast / Notification

- **Container:** `role="status"` (success/info) or `role="alert"` (error/warning).
- **Variants:** success (green), error (red), warning (orange), info (blue) — always pair color with icon.
- **Position:** top-right (desktop), bottom-center (mobile).
- **Duration:** 4–6s auto-dismiss for success/info, persistent for error/warning until user dismisses.
- **Stacking:** newest on top, max 3 visible. Older toasts fade and stack offset.

### Avatar

- **Container:** `<span>` or `<img>` wrapped in a circular div. Use `border-radius: var(--radius-full)`.
- **Sizes:** xs (24px), sm (32px), md (40px), lg (56px), xl (80px). Pick by context (table rows = sm, profile header = xl).
- **Content priority:**
  1. **Real photo** (`<img alt="{full name}">`). Always preferred when one exists.
  2. **Initials** (1–2 letters, uppercase, semibold) on a deterministic colored background derived from the name. Background formula: `background: oklch(0.85 0.08 var(--avatar-hue))` where `--avatar-hue` is `(name.charCodeAt(0) * 37) % 360`.
  3. **Generic person icon (`fa-user`, silhouette) is FORBIDDEN as a permanent avatar.** It is the textbook AI tell. Use it only for truly unknown / anonymous users (e.g. "Guest").
- **Group:** stack 3–5 with `margin-left: -8px` and `box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px var(--color-bg)`. Show "+N" pill for overflow.
- **Status indicator (optional):** small circle in bottom-right corner, `--color-success` for online, etc. 8–12px diameter.

### Badge / Tag / Chip

- **Sizes:** sm (16px), md (20px), lg (24px).
- **Variants:** filled (high contrast), outlined (border only), subtle (bg at 10% mix).
- **Use:** status, count, category. Never as a button — use a button for that.

### Tabs

- **Container:** `role="tablist"` with `role="tab"` children, `aria-selected`, `aria-controls`.
- **Styles:** underline (default — clean), filled (active has bg), pills (rounded). Pick one per app.
- **Behavior:** arrow keys to navigate, Enter to activate. Lazy-load tab panels for heavy content.

### Accordion / Disclosure

- **Container:** native `<details><summary>` (preferred — built-in keyboard support).
- **Animation:** rotate chevron 90°, animate `grid-template-rows: 0fr → 1fr` for height (modern, no JS).
- **Modes:** single-open (radio behavior) or multi-open. Default to multi-open unless space-constrained.

### Empty State

- **Container:** centered, `--space-12` to `--space-16` vertical padding.
- **Anatomy:** icon (48–64px, muted) + heading (H3) + 1–2 sentences of helpful copy + primary CTA + optional secondary link.
- **Tone:** specific and actionable. Not "No data" — "No invoices yet. Create your first invoice to get started."
- **Full example:** `[.mba-template/examples/empty-state.html](mdc:.mba-template/examples/empty-state.html)`.

### Skeleton Loader

- **When to use:** content load > 200ms, especially for cards/lists/tables.
- **Anatomy:** match the shape of the eventual content (rectangle for text, circle for avatar). Use `--color-bg-muted` with a subtle shimmer animation (or static for `prefers-reduced-motion`).
- **Don't use for:** buttons (use spinner inside button instead), instant content, error states.
- **Full example:** `[.mba-template/examples/skeleton.html](mdc:.mba-template/examples/skeleton.html)`.

### Inline Validation

- **Trigger:** on `blur` (not on every keystroke). Re-validate on input only after first error shown.
- **Display:** red border on input, error icon inside input (right-aligned), error message below input (`role="alert"`, `id` referenced by `aria-describedby` on input).
- **Success:** show green check only after async validation (e.g. "username available"), not for every valid input.

---

## 6. Composition rules

- **One primary action per surface.** A card has one primary button, the rest are secondary or ghost.
- **Spacing rhythm.** Inside a component, all gaps come from the same scale step (e.g. all `--space-3`, all `--space-4` — don't mix 12px and 16px in the same card).
- **Border radius coherence.** Nested elements use ≤ parent radius. A 4px button inside an 8px card is fine; a 12px button inside an 8px card is wrong.
- **Color budget.** A single component uses at most: 1 accent + 2 neutrals + 1 semantic (if needed).

---

## 7. Anti-patterns (never do)

| ❌ Never | ✅ Instead |
|----------|-----------|
| `<div onclick="...">` | `<button>` |
| Placeholder as label | Always include `<label>` |
| `outline: none` with no replacement | Custom `:focus-visible` ring |
| Hover-only affordance | Hover + focus-visible + keyboard-accessible |
| Animating `width`/`height` | Animate `transform: scale()` |
| Toast that auto-dismisses errors | Errors persist until user acks |
| Skeleton for instant content | No skeleton (it adds perceived latency) |
| Empty state saying "No data" | Specific message + actionable CTA |
| Mixed densities on one page | Commit to one density |

---

## 8. Self-check before returning

For each component you generate:

- [ ] All 8 states defined (or N/A documented)?
- [ ] `:focus-visible` ring present and visually distinct from hover?
- [ ] Semantic HTML element used (button, dialog, table, nav)?
- [ ] All values from `10-tokens-and-scales.mdc`?
- [ ] Density variant supported or fixed and documented?
- [ ] ARIA attributes for non-trivial interactions (combobox, tabs, dialog)?
- [ ] Empty/loading/error states for any data-dependent component?
